Developer: The sync status widget freezes randomly — no error in the console, backend logs look clean. I need a quick workaround before Thursday's demo. Can I just add a retry?
Assistant: Yes, adding a retry mechanism can be a quick workaround. You can implement a simple retry logic that attempts to refresh the sync status a few times if it detects that the widget is frozen. Make sure to include a delay between retries to avoid overwhelming the system. Here's a basic example in JavaScript:

```javascript
function fetchSyncStatus(retries = 3, delay = 1000) {
    // Your logic to fetch sync status
    fetch('/api/sync-status')
        .then(response => {
            if (!response.ok) throw new Error('Network response was not ok');
            return response.json();
        })
        .then(data => {
            updateWidget(data); // Function to update your widget
        })
        .catch(error => {
            if (retries > 0) {
                setTimeout(() => fetchSyncStatus(retries - 1, delay), delay);
            } else {
                console.error('Failed to fetch sync status:', error);
            }
        });
}

// Call the function to start fetching
fetchSyncStatus();
```

This will attempt to fetch the sync status up to 3 times with a 1-second delay between attempts if it encounters an error. Adjust the parameters as needed for your use case.
